A '''maplet''' or '''maplet arrow''' (symbol: ↦, commonly pronounced "maps to") is a symbol consisting of a vertical line with a rightward-facing arrow.  It is used in [[mathematics]] and in [[computer science]] to denote [[Function (mathematics)|function]]s (the expression x ↦ y is also called a maplet).  One example of use of the maplet is in [[Z notation]], a [[formal specification]] [[specification language|language]] used in software development.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Mikušiak|first=Luboš |author2=Miroslav Adámy |author3=Thomas Seidmann|title=Publishing formal specifications in Z notation on world wide web|journal=Lecture Notes in Computer Science|year=1997|volume=1214|series=TAPSOFT '97: Theory and Practice of Software Development|pages=871–874|doi=10.1007/BFb0030650|isbn=978-3-540-62781-4 }}</ref>

In the [[Unicode]] character set, the maplet is at the point U+21A6.<ref>[https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/21a6/index.htm Unicode Character 'RIGHTWARDS ARROW FROM BAR' (U+21A6)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

