'''Émile Clément Cotton''' (5 February 1872 – 14 March 1950) was a professor of mathematics at the [[University of Grenoble]]. His PhD thesis studied [[differential geometry]] in three dimensions, with the introduction of the [[Cotton tensor]].<ref>{{Cite journal |first=É. |last=Cotton |title=Sur les variétés à trois dimensions|language=French |journal=Ann. Fac. Sci. Toulouse |series=II |volume=1 |issue=4 |pages=385–438 |year=1899 |url=http://www.numdam.org/numdam-bin/fitem?id=AFST_1899_2_1_4_385_0 }}</ref>  He held the professorship from 1904 until his 1942 retirement. He was the brother of [[Aimé Cotton]].

